snippet: Foreign diplomats met with the Muslim Brotherhood’s chief strategist in a prison south of Cairo as part of an international effort to end Egypt’s political crisis.
abstract: United States envoy William J Burns meets with Khairat al-Shater, jailed leader of Muslim Brotherhood, in maximum-security prison on outskirts of Cairo; visit is part of intensifying international effort to end political crisis that began after Egypt’s security services deposed Pres Mohamed Morsi.
lead_paragraph: Foreign diplomats met with the Muslim Brotherhood’s chief strategist in a prison south of Cairo as part of an international effort to end Egypt’s political crisis.

headline.main: Envoys Visit a Top Islamist Inside a Jail Near Cairo
